cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper deals with the application of deep neural networks in retinal blood vessel segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the use of deep learning techniques, specifically deep convolutional neural networks, for feature learning, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of domain-specific prior knowledge to generate training samples, which could potentially fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
